<title>BELGIUM: Imperial Invest H1 1996/97 loss widens.</title>
<headline>Imperial Invest H1 1996/97 loss widens.</headline>
<dateline>BRUSSELS 1997-02-20</dateline>
<text>
<p>Six months to December 31, 1996</p>
<p>(in millions of Belgian francs, unless stated):</p>
<p>    Group net profit/loss	   46.8 loss  vs  34.9 loss</p>
<p>    Cons financial income	   12.8	 vs   6.7</p>
<p>    Cons capital gains/write backs 0.3	 vs  15.8</p>
<p>    Cons financial charges	  46.3	 vs  40.8</p>
<p>    Write downs/depreciations	8.8	 vs   1.6</p>
<p>NOTE - Imperial Invest is a Belgian family-controlled investment company. In a statement, the company noted that most of its dividend income is booked in its second half.</p>
